I think it's fine that AMD is dropping support for their older motherboards. It's pretty impressive that they were able to keep their compatibility for three generations despite the drastic changes to their CPU architecture. 

Then again, I might not be upset because I recently upgraded to an X570 mobo (with my first Ryzen, 3600X). To be honest though, I was almost certain that AMD was going to drop support for that mobo too when the next gen CPUs come out.
